               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; names of the donors; incipit of Text I; incipit of Text III; incipit of Text IV; note in the upper margin; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
In the incipit pages of Text I and III (fols. 4r, 172v), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text of the Vita represents the first of the two sub-types of the Däbrä Libanos recension of the Gädlä Täklä Haymanot (close, but not identical to the published text of the Vita, s. E.A.W. BUDGE (ed., tr.), The Life and Miracles of Takla Hâymânôt in the Version of Dabra Lîbânôs..., London 1906).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
